					<msContents>
						<summary>Memorial stone set up in honour of a cock, which fought for the western quarters (<foreign>mēl-cēri</foreign>) of a village. It is not clear whether the stone commemorates the death of the cock when fighting (as in the case of a deceased warrior) or its victorious fight.</summary>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc>
						<handDesc>
							<p>The <foreign>puḷḷi</foreign> is used. There are characters of eccentric ductus: <foreign>ku</foreign> and <foreign>k=ka</foreign> (line 2).</p>
						</handDesc>
					</physDesc>
				</msDesc>
